":"Ingredients"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"40 g olive oil"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 tbsp lemon juice"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"½ tsp salt"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"24 raw prawns, peeled and deveined"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"80 g brown onions, cut into halves"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 garlic cloves"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"500 g cucumbers, cut into pieces"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 lemon, cut into slices, each slice quartered"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"500 g water"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 heaped tsp Vegetable stock paste (refer to the recipe in The Basic Cookbook)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"¼ tsp ground black pepper"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"200 g full cream milk"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"40 g plain flour"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 tbsp fresh dill, leaves only (optional)"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","733 kJ \/ 175 kcal","12 g","10 g","9 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["If using frozen prawns, thaw before marinating.<br>- Unpeeled cucumbers add more colour and flavour to the soup.<br>- Long skewers can be cut to fit the Varoma dish.<br>- In hot weather serve this soup chilled. For a fresh summer flavour, replace dill with fresh mint or coriander.","Instead of flour use <b>150 g cooked<b> potatoes, cut into pieces, to thicken the soup.<br>- For a thicker soup, replace milk with pouring (whipping) cream.<br>- For a vegetarian option, replace prawns with small mushrooms <b>(3 cm),<b> feta cheese cubes, or tofu cubes marinated in soy sauce; and replace lemon slices with cherry tomatoes.<br>- Try adding a splash of dry white wine to the soup in the final step."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","35m","6 portions"]}